this paper examined mean IRAP scores (IRAP as DV), used IRAP scores to predict scale scores in regressions (IRAP as IV), and also reported zero order correlations. We report the latter here, as they are agnostic to prediction direction and not confounded by the partialling out of other variables.
for this and all other studies, correlations with full scales are exluded when their subscales are reported.

r = 0.494 was not included in the results, as results only reported correlations between the IRAP and some of the subscales of the OCI-R. Elsewhere, where all subscales are reported, we exclude the correlation with the total score and include only the subscales. Here we must do the opposite.
